413989469.text: "Mechanistically, the current model for insulin resistance in obesity suggests that adipose tissue macrophage (ATM) infiltration and proinflammatory cytokine release activates inflammatory pathways such as inhibitor of kappa B kinase beta (IKKbeta) and Jun NH 2 -terminal kinase (JNK), which impinge upon the insulin signaling cascade by inhibiting tyrosine phosphorylation of insulin receptor substrate 1 (IRS1), leading to impaired insulin activation of phosphoinositide 3-kinase (PI3K) and Akt."
